products.name: Hot Pockets Hickory Ham & Cheddar Cheese with Crispy Buttery Crust - 2 ct

extendedInfo.detail: Hickory ham & cheddar with reduced fat cheddar cheese & sauce in a crispy buttery crust.  9 g protein per sandwich. Per 1 Sandwich: 270 calories; 4 g sat fat (20% DV); 690 mg sodium (30% DV); 3 g total sugars; 160 mg calcium (10% DV); 2.3 mg iron (15% DV).  See nutrition information for sat fat and sodium content. Good source of protein.  Contains a bioengineered food ingredient.  Real satisfaction for real hunger. Nestle - Good food, good life. Fill up with the good stuff. It's what's on the inside that counts so we have options that are a good source of protein, made with real cheese, and a variety of delicious crusts all baked daily. Enjoy in an easy-to-hold sleeve. Gooey; Easy; Hot. Let's Talk. hotpockets.com, Text or call 1-800-350-5016.  Dispose responsibly.

extendedInfo.directions: Microwave Oven Cooking Instructions: For Hot Pockets Brand Sandwiches. Load it: Unwrap sandwich, load it into crisping sleeve, and place on paper plate. Heat it: Cook it in the magical heating machine, A.K.A. the microwave. Cooking Time on High: Quantity: 1 Sandwich; 1100 Watt Oven: 1:50 (Ovens vary; cooking time may need to be adjusted keep frozen. For food safety and quality, read and follow these cooking instructions to ensure product reaches internal temperature of 165 degrees F. Cook thoroughly before eating. Product will be hot! Save your tastebuds and wait for your sandwich to cool); Lower Wattage/Compact Microwave: 2:50 (Ovens vary; cooking time may need to be adjusted keep frozen. For food safety and quality, read and follow these cooking instructions to ensure product reaches internal temperature of 165 degrees F. Cook thoroughly before eating. Product will be hot! Save your tastebuds and wait for your sandwich to cool). Quantity: 2 Sandwiches; 1100 Watt Oven: 3:30 (Ovens vary; cooking time may need to be adjusted keep frozen. For food safety and quality, read and follow these cooking instructions to ensure product reaches internal temperature of 165 degrees F. Cook thoroughly before eating. Product will be hot! Save your tastebuds and wait for your sandwich to cool); Lower Wattage/Compact Microwave: For best results, cook one at a time. Enjoy it. Let sit 2 minutes to complete cooking, and enjoy. Conventional Oven: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F, unwrap sandwich and place on baking sheet. Do not use crisping sleeve in oven. Bake for 26 minutes (Ovens vary; cooking time may need to be adjusted keep frozen. For food safety and quality, read and follow these cooking instructions to ensure product reaches internal temperature of 165 degrees F. Cook thoroughly before eating. Product will be hot! Save your tastebuds and wait for your sandwich to cool), then carefully remove from oven. Air Fryer: Try Frying for an even crispier crunch! Unwrap Sandwich and place in bottom of air fryer. Do not use crisping sleeve in air fryer. Do not use crisping sleeve in air fryer. For 1 sandwich, set Air Fryer at 360 degrees F for 16 Minutes (Directions develop using various sized air fryers; cook times may need to be adjusted). For 2 sandwiches, place separately and set Air Fryer at 360 degrees F for 18 minutes (Directions develop using various sized air fryers; cook times may need to be adjusted). Carefully remove from air fryer. Cook thoroughly.  Keep frozen.  Best when used by date stamped on box.
